1.  Facility Policy: The owners, management and employees of Wymore Fertilizer/Filley are committed to the prevention of any accidental releases of anhydrous ammonia. If An accidental release should occur, the facility is prepared to work with the local fire department and law enforcement personnel to migigate any releases to the population and the environment of our community.



2. Facility Information:  Wymore Fertilizer/Filley employees are based at Wymore Fertilizer Office location and go to  the premise of Wymore Fertilizer/Filley as needed. There are 0 full time eployees at this site.  The primary activity at this location is the storage of anhydrous ammonia for sale to farmers. Anhydrous ammonia received and stored while awaiting deliver to the farmers. The maximum amount of anhydrous ammonia stored at this facility is approximately 80,000 pounds. During periods of non operation, of this facility, our employees will conduct inspections of this facility. Anything out of the ordinary is reported to local law enforcement and to the owner of said facility and appropriate action is taken.



3.  Accidental Release Prevention Program: The facility has implemented the provisions of Safety Requirements for the storage and handling of anhydrous ammonia published by the American National Standards Institute and the Standard of the U.S. Occupational Safety and Health Administration, Storage and Handling of anhydrous ammonia.



4.  Five Year Accident History: Wymore Fertilizer/Filley has leased said premise spring 2010 and purchased the anhydrous ammonia equipment located on said premise also spring 2010. There has been no accidental releases of anhydrous ammonis that have caused any deaths, injuries, or significant property damage at this facility, nor to our knowledge have resulted in offsite deaths, injuries, evacuations, property damage, or environmental damage.



5.  Emergency Response Program: Our facility has contacted the local responders and we do not plan to

have our employees respond to a major release.



6.   Planned Changes to Improve Safety: Safety improvements will be an on going process at our facility.Periodic evaluations will be performed to assess our prevention and safety programs.
